1
00:00:02,472 --> 00:00:04,548
That was a good day, wasn’t it?

2
00:00:04,548 --> 00:00:08,266
Cardiff, the market, the castle… bet your feet are tired now.

3
00:00:08,617 --> 00:00:11,698
Nope! We should walk home! It’s too nice for the bus!

4
00:00:12,048 --> 00:00:14,968
All the way? Up the canal walk? That’s a long one, love.

5
00:00:15,319 --> 00:00:19,437
I’m not scared! And we might see otters!

6
00:00:19,786 --> 00:00:19,806
(chuckles)

7
00:00:19,786 --> 00:00:30,527
Alright then, the long way it is.

8
00:00:30,878 --> 00:00:32,792
Off the train, Newport lights glow,

9
00:00:32,792 --> 00:00:34,628
Feet hit the pavement, nowhere to go.

10
00:00:34,628 --> 00:00:36,542
Day full of laughter, market stalls bright,

11
00:00:36,542 --> 00:00:38,378
Castle stood tall in the morning light.

12
00:00:38,378 --> 00:00:40,451
But now the sun's hanging low in the west,

13
00:00:40,451 --> 00:00:42,128
Still too warm to let the night rest.

14
00:00:42,128 --> 00:00:43,722
No rush, no ride, no need to roam,

15
00:00:43,722 --> 00:00:45,368
We'll take the long way home.

16
00:00:45,718 --> 00:00:48,031
Past the old docks, down by the quay,

17
00:00:48,031 --> 00:00:49,866
Lanterns flicker where the river plays free.

18
00:00:49,866 --> 00:00:51,862
Canal path calls, soft earth, stone,

19
00:00:51,862 --> 00:00:53,697
Water runs quiet where the willows have grown.

20
00:00:53,697 --> 00:00:55,771
She skips ahead, arms out wide,

21
00:00:55,771 --> 00:00:57,686
Counting the ripples, chasing the tide.

22
00:00:57,686 --> 00:01:01,356
Look, a heron! Quiet now, see? She whispers low, pulling on me.

23
00:01:01,356 --> 00:01:03,350
Dragonflies dart where the reeds stand tall,

24
00:01:03,350 --> 00:01:05,186
Minnows scatter by the old stone wall

25
00:01:05,186 --> 00:01:07,260
Owls start calling as dusk takes hold,

26
00:01:07,260 --> 00:01:08,905
Sky draped deep in lilac and gold.

27
00:01:09,254 --> 00:01:13,004
Take the long way, slow and free,

28
00:01:13,004 --> 00:01:15,878
Through the woods, by the sea.

29
00:01:15,878 --> 00:01:20,584
Hand in hand, step by step,

30
00:01:20,584 --> 00:01:24,144
These are the days we won’t forget.

31
00:01:24,495 --> 00:01:26,409
Shadows stretch, streetlamps hum,

32
00:01:26,409 --> 00:01:28,165
Fox darts quick where the brambles run.

33
00:01:28,165 --> 00:01:30,079
She hums an old tune, soft and clear,

34
00:01:30,079 --> 00:01:32,153
A song I once sang in her toddler years.

35
00:01:32,153 --> 00:01:34,069
Bridge up ahead, water runs black,

36
00:01:34,069 --> 00:01:36,063
Ripples break where the otters track.

37
00:01:36,063 --> 00:01:37,819
Dad, do you think they know our names?

38
00:01:37,819 --> 00:01:39,653
Maybe they do, wild things play games.

39
00:01:39,653 --> 00:01:43,722
We stop, breathe in, lanterns glow,

40
00:01:43,722 --> 00:01:46,963
Steps slowing where moonlight flows.

41
00:01:47,313 --> 00:01:49,995
I love this walk, I don’t want it to end.

42
00:01:50,346 --> 00:01:52,579
Some roads never really do, love.

43
00:01:52,579 --> 00:01:54,942
We just keep walking them in our hearts.

44
00:01:55,293 --> 00:01:59,121
Take the long way, slow and free,

45
00:01:59,121 --> 00:02:02,712
Through the woods, by the sea.

46
00:02:02,712 --> 00:02:06,382
Hand in hand, step by step,

47
00:02:06,382 --> 00:02:10,262
These are the days we won’t forget.

48
00:02:10,611 --> 00:02:14,201
Night folds in, stars shine bright,

49
00:02:14,201 --> 00:02:17,394
Breath turns mist in the silver light.

50
00:02:17,394 --> 00:02:21,782
Footsteps softer, the world so still,

51
00:02:21,782 --> 00:02:40,900
Just us, the trees, the air so chill.

52
00:02:41,250 --> 00:02:43,164
Crosskeys passed, lights in sight,

53
00:02:43,164 --> 00:02:45,080
Cottage waiting, warm and bright.

54
00:02:45,080 --> 00:02:46,835
Door swings open, firelight glows,

55
00:02:46,835 --> 00:02:48,909
She kicks off her shoes, stretching her toes.

56
00:02:48,909 --> 00:02:50,745
I pull down a book, pages worn,

57
00:02:50,745 --> 00:02:52,580
She curls up close, safe and warm.

58
00:02:52,580 --> 00:02:54,653
Eyes grow heavy as the firelight plays,

59
00:02:54,653 --> 00:02:56,459
Drifting off slow as the night-time sways.

60
00:02:56,808 --> 00:03:00,318
Take the long way, slow and free,

61
00:03:00,318 --> 00:03:04,068
Through the woods, by the sea.

62
00:03:04,068 --> 00:03:07,979
Hand in hand, step by step,

63
00:03:07,979 --> 00:03:15,527
These are the days we won’t forget.

64
00:03:15,877 --> 00:03:17,203
You’re asleep already, aren’t you?

65
00:03:17,552 --> 00:03:17,573
(yawn)

66
00:03:17,552 --> 00:03:22,468
Mmmh… still walking…

67
00:03:22,818 --> 00:03:22,838
(chuckle)

68
00:03:22,818 --> 00:03:23,266
Goodnight, little star
